The Ogun State Government has announced that one coronavirus death has been recorded in the state. The announcement was made by the state Ministry of Health in a tweet via its Twitter account on Saturday. The Ministry also confirmed that 21 new cases of the viral infection have been recorded in the state. The tweet reads “Ogun COVID-19 Update. “21 New confirmed cases, 1 Death, 316 active cases. “Ogun State has recorded 21 new confirmed cases across three LGAs, on 12th June 2020. “This brings the total number of cases so far confirmed to 544. “Sadly, one death has also been recorded bringing to 14 the total number of deaths reported in the state.” Meanwhile, Nigeria now has a total of 15,181 confirmed COVID-19 cases.